          <num>353-30</num>
          <heading>Others by permission</heading>
          <content>
            <p>§353-30  Others by permission.
Only
official visitors shall be allowed to visit any state correctional facility or
to have any oral or written communication with a committed person, unless with
the written permission of the administrator of the correctional facility or the
director.  No visitor shall deliver to or receive from any committed person any
letter or message except with permission granted by the administrator of a
state correctional facility pursuant to rules adopted by the director or
facility administrator.  Unauthorized communications, passing of documents, or
visiting shall be a class C felony. [L 1987, c 338, pt of §3]
